# Documentation maintenance

When you change code under `app-pwa/`, `backend-ts/`, or `supabase/`:

1. Update the relevant file(s) in `docs/` (see [docs/README.md](../../docs/README.md) for the map).
2. Add an entry to [docs/changelog.md](../../docs/changelog.md) with date and sections: Changed, Added, Fixed, Security, Database, Docs (omit empty sections).
3. Do not invent behavior — if unsure, mark `TODO: verify` in the doc.
4. Do not paste secrets or `.env` values into markdown.

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| Auth, sessions, CSRF, roles | `docs/auth-security.md`, possibly `docs/SECURITY.md` |
| API routes, guards, crons | `docs/backend.md`, `docs/architecture.md` |
| PWA routes, composables, UX | `docs/frontend.md`, `docs/features.md` |
| Migrations, RLS, RPCs | `docs/database.md`, `docs/database-schema-conventions.md` |
| Credits, Stripe, plans | `docs/payments-credits.md` |
| Uploads, storage | `docs/uploads.md` |
| Notifications, alerts | `docs/notifications.md` |
| Env vars, deploy | `docs/deployment.md`, `.env.example` |
| New product feature | `docs/features.md` |

Keep edits concise; link to existing runbooks instead of duplicating them.
